  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Counsellor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Department</strong></p>\n<p>COMIT</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Key Position Objectives</strong></p>\n<p>Provide counselling and case management of clients of Club HEAL.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Duties &amp; Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<p>· To provide assessment, psychosocial interventions which includes case management and appropriate therapy(s) for clients with mental health issues and dementia, including their caregivers.</p>\n<p>· Develop individualised intervention programmes (psychotherapy and counselling)</p>\n<p>· Case manage and work closely with the multidisciplinary recovery/dementia team for each client and their caregivers (assess needs and develop care plans)</p>\n<p>· Provide clients and their caregivers with education, training and support to equip and enable them to live well in the community</p>\n<p>· Liaise with other service care providers of persons with Mental Health conditions/caregivers as needed</p>\n<p>· Up-to-date reporting of each person with Mental Health conditions /caregiver</p>\n<p>· To work closely with and utilise existing community mental health system and process for helping to coordinate patients to other forms of care if necessary</p>\n<p>· Any other duties assigned by COMIT Manager</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Technical Competencies:</strong></p>\n<p>· Genuine interest in others</p>\n<p>· Empathy and understanding.</p>\n<p>· Ability to listen – On multiple levels</p>\n<p>· Ability to relate to and adapt communication style to suit a wide range of people.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Core Competencies:</strong></p>\n<p>· Required to contribute to the cause of the company and break the stigma related to mental health.</p>\n<p>· Resilient, passionate to service the community and a team player.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Preferred achievements / characteristics:</strong></p>\n<p>· Bachelors or Masters in Counselling, Psychology or Social Work </p>\n<p>· 2-3 years of relevant working experience in Social Service Sector or Mental Health Sector</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Any other duties as assigned by Reporting Officer.</strong></p>",
